{"questionId":"9071721","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The structure of an organic molecule can help predict the type of reaction it can undergo.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Improvements in instrumentation have made identification of organic compounds&nbsp;routine.</p>\n<p>The empirical formula of an unknown compound containing a phenyl group was found&nbsp;to be C<sub>4</sub>H<sub>4</sub>O. The molecular ion peak in its mass spectrum appears at <em>m</em>/<em>z </em>= 136.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Deduce the molecular formula of the compound.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>«</strong><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{136}}{{48 + 4 + 16}} = 2\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>136</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>48</mn>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mn>4</mn>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mn>16</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n</math></span><strong>»</strong></p>\n<p>C<sub>8</sub>H<sub>8</sub>O<sub>2</sub></p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9071721","referenceCode":"18M.2.sl.TZ2.7c.i","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Deduce the molecular formula of the compound.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"c.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 11: Measurement and data processing","11.3 Spectroscopic identification of organic compounds","Core","Topic 11: Measurement and data processing"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}